reviews.review_text: Hands down, best fish and chips Ive ever had in my life. We got the halibut and chips - fish tasted so fresh, was flaky in the inside and had a great exterior crunch. I must say though, the chips (i.e. fries), was the star of the dish for me - they were cooked to perfection. Crunchy on the outside and fluffy on the inside, every single one of them. Service was quick and the patio atmosphere with a good view just makes this place that much better. Its about a 5min walk from Granville Island. 10000000% would recommend this place to anyone that loves good food.

The tuna sandwich was okay, but the Halibut and Chips were amazing!! Meaty with light crispy batter that melts in your mouth.. Highly recommend the fish & chips!! Nice small outdoor spot by the docks across from Granville Island. Sandwich was a 3/5 Halibut was 7/5

To be concise.. yes, I would recommend. Pro: delicious. Good portions. Very friendly staff (exceptional customer service) Con: parking is difficult. No indoor or covered seating. We tried the Cod fish and chips. Excellent batter and the fries were delicious. Tatar sauce was rich and satisfying. Coleslaw was underwhelming and slightly boring. We also had the Oyster  Po Boy  sandwich. The flavour was amazing and unique. Highly recommend. Overall, great service and exciting sandwich menu. Fish and chips were above par. I wished there were some covered seating as you re completely exposed to the elements. Of note: walking distance to Granville Island! Also, expect to wait to be served during peak hours.

Amazing!!! Wanted fish and chips and I could not have been more pleased. Best I ve ever had. Staff was great and you can see them cutting up the fish to order so couldn t be fresher. Do not hesitate to visit.

Spectacular fish and chips and other delicacies (fish tacos and burgers) at this modest shack near Granville Island. The cod is fresh and super tasty, perfectly cooked! The chips (French fries) are excellent, the tuna taco is worth a trip. With CAD 10 per person you eat like a king. Best food in a long time! The service is super friendly. The accommodation is a bit rustic but hey  you can take the goodies out and eat it in your own castle!

Super tasty Fish & Chips! I went a couple of times and it was  amazing, the Halibut and the Salmon were delicious  . I also tried the Tuna Sandwich, super tasty with the wasabi mayo. The only downside was, that in one of my visits they made a mistake on my order and instead of trying to fix it they were really rude.

The perfect way to end your day visiting Granville Island. This fish and chips shack is worth the walk over from the main market area. The staff here is super friendly and the food is cooked to order. We got the cod fish and chips basket, and it tasted so fresh and high quality! The portions here are huge so honestly one plate is big enough to share between two people. The dish also comes with an amazing sesame tasting slaw on the side. Don t skip this place!

The captain of our zodiac boat trip recommended Go Fish! for lunch and told us that it was one of the best places to get fish and chips. He was right. Its basically a shack that you walk up to and put in your order. Nothing fancy. Simple and really good. We found a table by the side of the restaurant so we could  look over the bay.

This is the legit place for fish and chips. Fresh line-caught fish and amazing flavour at a fair price in a great location. My partner got their grilled salmon sandwich and it was epic, just the right seasoning and sauce. My fried halibut was a good portion and perfectly battered. The fries were incredible, but I into the age-old problem of my girlfriend stealing half of them. Last but not least, the staff were all amazing! The cashier and cooks were the nicest people. Their quality of work proves they care, and I loved their taste in music.

Outside seating only with a great view of the bay, fishing boats and the Vancouver skyline. Gets very busy during lunch hours. However the fish and chips are great, very crispy. I ordered 2 piece cod and chips and it was enough for my partner and I. For fish and chip places in metro vancouver, this is one of the better places.
Great food, spectacular view, lovely girl taking the orders. The service is alright. I got the halibut and chips which was delicious and the portion was quite large. Food
Fish batter could have used a little more seasoning, but this was a great place to grab fish and chips and hang out by the water. The salmon tacos were good too.

BEST fish and chips Ive ever had in my life! We waited a full hour in the sun and got heat stroke (wish they had more shaded areas available for the queue / lineup folks or folks waiting to get their food) but it was worth it!!!!
Best of the best with amazing view of Granville Island and Burrard Bridge. Seating is outdoors or take back to your car, so dress appropriately!

go fish is my favorite fish and chip place. The place is small but nice, besides that it is in a very quiet and beautiful location where you can go for a walk. The amount is big for the price that you pay. I highly recommend it.
Great shack on False Creek beside Granville Island serving excellent fish and chips.  Our group had both cod and halibut.  The fries were also great.

This food stand near Fishermens Wharf has standard fish and chips with 3 fish options and other seafood creations like sandwiches and tacones. I had never tried oysters before but was feeling adventurous when I came and ordered the oyster po boy. I obviously wouldnt have known what oysters are supposed to be like, but I thought these were really good, and the sandwich as a whole was awesome. The grilled onions and chipotle sauce were really tasty with the oysters. The side of coleslaw was nice and crisp, and I always love coleslaw so I was happy this was included. The prices have gone up since the most recent menu pictures were uploaded online, but theyre still pretty reasonable for the times. My sandwich was $16. Theres a small, partially covered seating area to enjoy your food. It was raining while I was there and everyone was packing in to stay dry, but it wasnt unpleasant - it kind of added to the experience. Even in the rain, the setting by the water and fish market is perfect - this is how seafood is meant to be eaten! And although service may not be the most important thing at a counter-service place like this, the person who took my order was pleasant and made me feel welcome even with our short exchange. Vegetarian options: Everything contains seafood. Nothing vegetarian.

Expect a line up at this spot upon opening till closing - line does go by relatively quick. Limited seating on the patio but they have some expanded shared picnic tables near the parking area. Food here is great - from portions, quality of taste/fish, fresh fry to the coleslaw. The ratio of batter to fish is dominated by the meaty fish but the thin crisp outer layer works well in taste balance. Meals start from $11-> $24 depending on portion and which fish choice. Must go when in the area. Parking: Very limited parking
If you like fish and chips, ya gotta try Go Fish. The fish was fresh, not greasy, flavorful.  Just go do it.

From the first moment, i got there, I loved everything about that place. From the fries to the fish everything was delicious, even the coleslaw. Honestly, the beer bather around the fish (cod in my case) was good and light. When I said I loved everything, I meant it. Their fires are astonishing, crispy and homestyle like.

This place is well worth the walk. We were waiting in line in the Market and a local told us about this place. So we decided to head over and it was worth the 5 minute walk. Everyone will tell you this is the best fish and chips and they are right. I will go further to tell you that the Curry soup, is to die for. It s incredible, and has fresh fish in it. The salad, is made with a homemade vinaigrette and was also simple and wonderful. This little food stand is a gem, and the folks who know.. know. This is it.

Fish and chips were perfect. We got the Cod (they were out of Halibut at 2pm) and it tasted very fresh! Were planning to go again next time to try the Halibut hopefully. We waited for about 1h, including time for our food to get ready.

Delicious, seafood dishes. We got the salmon sandwich and the cod fish and chips. It was a 15 minute line to order and then a 30 minute wait for the food. But when the food came it was very fresh and hot. The salmon was a great sandwich with just a little bit of char to let you know that it was just cooked. The fish and chips where regular fish and chips but the fish (cod) was extremely flaky which made it so soft to eat. I would definitely get the fish and chips as the value of this dish is better than the salmon sandwich.

Always the BEST I always take my Mom here, delicious. Only reason I didnt give it 5 stars is I got an overdone piece of cod and it was chewy. By time I examined it, we were off to the side facing water and didnt feel like taking back, which Im sure they would have replaced piece. Great staff. Sometimes a long lineup Its $20. For 2piece cod and chips. Up quite a bit since pandemic.

One of the best place for fish and chips!! Highly recommended this place. Place is next to seawall and has such a great view if its a good weather. The batter tasted phenomenal. It has such a great crunch. One of the best price for fish and chips. Hopefully price won t go up due to inflation. Must try if you love fish and chips

The kitchen music can be loud and metal, the staff can seem overwhelmed and have a hard time hearing over the music, the picnic tables can be full, the lineup can be long and everything can be a little wet from a recent rain ... This is still *by far* the best place to go for halibut and chips in Vancouver. Its a pilgrimage for us ... The beginning of summer, the end of summer, the first really glorious day of spring ... Its a Go Fish celebration. Two pieces of halibut and chips with a soda and tip costs close to $40, but it feeds two easily.

Still my favorite fish n chips shack.  We miss the scallop burgers but the oyster burgers were just as good.  They were out of halibut but the cod was a great alternative.  Great portions.   We really enjoyed the tacones as well.  No sheltered seating and the area lacks parking.

One of the best fish and chips we ve had! The fish is of good quality and the serving sizes are great! Tried the cod, halibut and a tuna sandwich. Both fish were cooked well - moist, crunchy and light batter, not too oily and well-seasoned. The fries are crispy and they use good quality potatoes too. The sandwich was delicious but I would rather order fish and chips! Great for a day out to Granville island and making the walk to this location is definitely worth it!

Amazing fish and chips the best I have had in decades. Just a little shack with some tables and the wharf but oh boy it was amazing. Well priced about $21 to $28 for 2 pieces with chips. So good the wife and I went back and ordered a 3rd order to split between us.

EVERYTIME I come to Vancouver I HAVE TO COME HERE. I don t care if it s raining cats and dogs outside. Hurricane Katrina could be going on and I wouldn t even notice cause I would be too engulfed in my delicious fish & chips and curry soup. The staff are SO friendly, and hilarious! The food is amazing, consistent, and delightful. The Halibut is to die for, and the chips are fried to perfection. The oyster Po boy is also amazing! Honestly, I ve never had anything from here that didn t make me melt in my seat from sheer joy and sensory overload.

Absolutely great fish and chips, comfortable quiet place with great dockside seating, and man do the staff have character! Laughing, joking, singing, it definitely makes you feel good because when the staff put their heart into a place, you can count on great food.

Someone recommended this place as a must visit at Granville Island. And it didn t disappoint us and a quite popular spot I must say. It was a 15-minute line to order and then a 30-minute wait for the food during the lunch time in the mid-September. But when the food came it was very fresh, crispy & soft inside. One of the best places for fish and chips within reasonable price, situated next to seawall and has such a great view if it s a good weather

AMAZING Fish n Chips in an awesome setting. Came from Edmonton to check out Vancouver and wanted to checkout some great food places that wont break the bank. Go Fish is one of them and my oh my does it impress! It is quite a popular spot, so the wait time can take anywhere from 10-20 minutes during the lunch hour. But its worth it. Food came out fresh & crispy, the price was VERY reasonable and you have great views of the harbor & Vancouver. HIGHLY recommend it for anyone visiting or is from the local area.

Hands down, best fish and chips Ive had in Canada (so far).  We ordered the halibut.  The batter was very flavourful, and the fish was still moist on the inside.  The fries were also very good, and tasted like it came from a big french fry chain.  The fish overall did not feel too heavy, and did not feel too salty.  Definitely worth the 30 minute wait.
The oyster burger is light, yet meaty and I prefer their fish and oyster sandwiches instead of fish and chips (Personal preference). Great fresh seafood overall!

Its more like a food truck with an open space in front of it where they put some tables and chairs. Awesome for a sunny day. But when its raining you should grab your food and go. The food is so yummy. Fish and chips and salmon sandwich were both very tasty.
Their fish and chips are amazing, worth many visits again and again. The best thing to do is order some foods and spend your time sitting there and enjoying the scenery by the water.

Nice little hidden gem.  We got there about 2 pm and they were starting to sell out of items.  But the food was worth the wait and scenery made the wait worthwhile.  Fish batter wasnt too heavy or super thick, the chips were crispy and can tell they take care of the oil. I suggest getting there early to beat the rush. But definitely worth the wait.
We tried one of each fish and honestly the oyster burger was the best Ive ever had.

Wow Amazing. What a treat, first impressions first of all I love that its outsider it was my first time coming here today and I love the fish the service was very good people are friendly and the FISH was amazing I got the halibut and the cod with chips and cola with coleslaw on the side and tarter sauce with another spicy dipping sauce. The fish is deep fried but it was not heavy at all. When I was finished I was totally satisfied and I felt great, I didnt want to fall asleep or anything it gave me power and energy for my day. Cant wait to come back again. Thank you GoFish

Really good fish and chips! Halibut was too thick though, tasted like fillet. Very generous but would be better if the halibut was thinner. Cod piece was good. The proportion of batter and fish was perfect. Fries were good too!

Totally worth the 45-minute wait: and the small upside was they told us it would be about 45/60mins wait when we ordered. Cod and Halibut were perfectly cooked, flakey and moist. Batter was seasoned, thick enough to hold vinegar but somehow not stodgy or greasy. To top it off, chips literally could not have been crispier. Only thing I would change: ask for more ketchup next time for chip dipping! Definitely will be back for my next serve of fish and chips.

I have to say I finally had best fish and chips. It s always long line up but it s really worth it and please go there before 1pm because they might sold out halibuts. I was lucky that I had last two of them. One thing I really happy about my meal was not so greasy and halibuts were so fresh. Also the seats were enough amount for everyone no one was eating without seat.

A great experience! We had 1 piece salmon and chips and 1 piece cod and chips. OMG! There was actually fish in the fish and chip ( unlike at Vancouver Fish Company!) The portions were very generous, too. (Unlike at the Vancouver Fish Company.) Tasted great, price was very reasonable and the staff were super friendly. A very pleasant experience. Will definitely be taking ALL my out of town visitors here.
Love the Po Boy burgers. Worth a visit on a sunny warm day. Check if they are opened before visiting to avoid disappointment. You can walk to Granville island from here. Highly recommended.

This place is highly rated, and deservedly so. We re here Sunday at 12:10, about 10 minutes after they open.  There is a 20 min wait in line to order already, and by the time we ordered, the wait for the food is about 20 min.  The folks working there were friendly, and shouted out the long wait time to everyone so they know what to expect.  Didn t see anyone leave though. Very simple Menu, Cod, Salmon, or Halibut and Chips, along with a Salmon  Taco  or wrap.  The daily special was a Tuna wrap, along with a red curry soup. We ordered a bit of everything, and everything was good!  The fried cod and Salmon had a crunchy batter, and the fish was very fresh.  The fish was served on a bamboo basket filled with fresh fries that were crunchy, and a really big serving.  The tar tar sauce and the slaw was very good too, but the cod was really good with ketchup as well. The tuna wrap was tasty, the flavors were very balanced, and enhanced the freshness and sweetness of the tuna. All in all, we ate too much, but we will be going back.  The long lines were longer when we were done, but folks were waiting patiently for it.

This is a tiny take out fish and chip place. It packs a punch with your tastebuds though. The fish, chips, coleslaw and tartar sauce were so delicious! Good prices and large portions. A definite must try for anyone. Two thumbs up

Really tasty fish and chips super close to granville island. I like taking mine on my walk with me along the seawall and snacking the whole walk. I ordered three pieces of cod with fries, and I find thats a good amount for two people.

Great dockside fish n chip spot just off the beaten path of Granville island. Food was great! Watching the boats, and the city skyline are great views and the guys in the kitchen are friendly. Don t expect table service, but that s what makes this place authentic. Also beware of seagulls!

My teenager and I shared one plate of two pieces, plus fries. It was plenty as a snack. It was delicious and the prices are reasonable. Also, the view is fantastic and Granville Island market is within five minutes walk. The staff are friendly, plenty of seats. Free parking just a few feet away. Yaaay! You have to go there and have some fresh fish...they have tacos as well...Will have that next time. Im so lucky, I just need to cross the Burrard bridge and bingo! This is my new favorite fish and chips. Go Fish!

Great location. Chips and fish was excellent taste. Special is sauces. I really had a good time there. At the weekend is too busy and crowded here. We just ordered and take away. I sure will be back to try another type of food

By far the best fish Ive ever had. Im a tourist from Toronto so I wanted some local fish n chips and this place far exceeded my expectations.  friendly staff and out of this world fish and tar tar sauce (make sure you by extra, I could drink the stuff) made my first local fish experience one I wont soon forget.
The best fish and chips I have ever had. The batter is so thin and not greasy whatsoever. The fries are fresh cut. I highly recommend Go Fish. Get there early, there will be a line up.
Amazing Fish and Chips place! The Halibut was crazy good! Very good food! The ocean and Granville island view is amazing! The service was so fast! Staff are so nice and friendly! Highly recommended!
This is a great place to stop for fish n chips while walking or biking.  Just be aware the portions are quite generous. I only finished half of my chips.

Wow! This was a fantastic experience. First off it is right on the harbor. The fish is tender and fresh. We both had fish and chips. It was the best fish and chips I have very had. Other patrons tried the sandwich and tacos options which also looked good. Its a small menu which I like. It takes about 20 minutes for the food to be ready as it is fresh made to order. This place is worth the wait in line.

Their salmon burger is absolutely amazing, I inhale every bite of it every time. The staff are fun and friendly and even though the line ups are long, their food tell you why. Its great to grab a bite and sit outside in the park to enjoy the view of the bridge and pier. Awesome place.
Fresh and delicious. Definitely check this place out.

The halibut fish and chips were the best Ive had in Canada, hands down. Stayed crispy and cooked to perfection. The staff were also incredibly friendly; the young lady working the till in particular should be commended.

We got the halibut and chips. Cost for this was $19  which honestly seems like an excellent price considering serving size and quality. The halibut was thick and well-cooked. The batter was perfect as well. It was pouring rain when we went. A server pulled out the canopy and wiped down all the benches and tables for us, which was very courteous. We would definitely recommend this place!!
Had a halibut with chips and tuna salad, both were so yummy! The wait was a bit longer just because they were so busy! Strongly recommended!!!
Lucky for us, we meet a New York and recommend us this place! We had a really good lunch and honestly it was very fresh, and tasty highly recommend tuna grill sandwich and fries! Food : 5/5

we ordered two of the fish and chips; one with salmon and the other was halibut (i think) but, it doesnt matter because both orders of fish were delicious! the view was top notch and its a short walk from Granville which was enjoyable. the only downfall was that the fries were extremely salty we left some behind. although, besides that the staff is a bunch of young guys which is a nice atmosphere and funny when you hear them talking to each other and working
Great fish! We shared halibut x2 and a piece of cod with fries. They even gave us each a serving of coleslaw! Good price, batter was delicious and fries were decent!

Unbelievably good!  It was a must stop every time we came to Vancouver and literally a notable point when considering moving to Van.  Now that we live here we go all the time and easily the second best fish and chips I ve ever had.  Wait times can be long but I do it every time and no regrets.  Halibut fish and chips is worth the extra price.
One of the best thing you can do it in Vancouver if you want real street fish and chips! Excellent in all senses, seriously! Great quality-price. 10/10.

This place is a container. Converted into sort of like a food truck,but no truck... Beware there is no indoor seating. The place is open 12 months of the year. And it s interesting to go eat there in the winter and eat outside in the chilli brisk cool ocean air. You cannot beat the view with a backdrop of the city Granville Island and all the fishing boats. The food is fresh and at times in limited quantities. This place serves exactly what you would expect battered cod or salmon or any of the other seafood they sell to be. The service can be a little annoying only because there s so many tourists in front of you who don t know how to read a menu. Or ask to many questions And delay the line. Outdoor seating is probably for 50. But you can easily sit on the seawall and enjoy your snack. Beware of the birds they might steal your meal when you re not looking. My photos of the fish tacos. They were pretty good. Not enough for an entire meal. But a great snack while walking along the seawall.

The very best halibut - and honestly best fish and chips - Ive ever had. Crispy amd creamy and fresh and delightful. Coleslaw and tartar sauce are great. Patio has heaters and is warm and covered during the rain. So rain or shine, go. Go fish.
Best fish and chips I ve ever had. Cods were THICC BOIS and the fries were crisp and well seasoned. Bit of a wait but definitely worth it
Very nice place on the side of the pier. Staff is very friendly, and the food is so so good!!
Went right when it opened and there still was a line! But well worth the wait - I can definitely see what all the hype is about. The crunch on their batter and fries were 10/10!!!

A local favourite for fish and chips. I always think of this place when Im craving fish and chips. Its just a pain to get here by car, much easier if you bike. The fish and fries they serve is piping hot. The ratio of batter to fish is perfect. We biked go a park close by to enjoy our crispy fish and chips.

Great fish and chips! And Im from the UK, so I know what Im talking about.   Youll be sat outside in the sun/rain/whatever and I didnt spy any restrooms but its the best fish Ive had in 8 years in Canada. Wheelchair accessibility: There is a step up to get to the window to order and I didnt see any accommodations for wheelchairs to be able to access the platform.

Delicious fish and chips at affordable prices. I got a piece cod fish with chips at about $13. It has a small outdoor seating area that s not heated so it got quite cold on a cold windy day. The person giving us the food was absolutely funny and energetic! And that made the experience even better.

Truly amazing fish and chips! My boyfriend and I shared an order of 2 pc cod + chips. Fish done perfectly (fluffy and almost creamy texture) with a great batter, and fries are also just an amazing crisp and you can just tell that they use quality potatoes! Amazing service! The cashier was outstandingly friendly! Theyre doing takeout only (patio closed) because of COVID, but there are plenty of places nearby to chow down Im definitely going to come back to this place and tell all my friends about it. I heard that theres usually a wait, but we were lucky to beat the line at about 5:45pm on a Wednesday A true 10/10 experience
Some of the freshest and best fish and chips I  ever had! It was so so so good. Would definitely come back here if I ever come back to Vancouver!
My favourite fish n chips to date. Crispy, fresh, and flavourful. I recommend going early, and be prepared for long wait times as it is a very popular place
Simply delicious! Fantastically fresh fish, perfectly fried. Loved the Asian spin on the coleslaw with sesame oil. Refreshing.
Excellent fish and chips, best in the city. Great professional staff. Wait times can be long as it is such a popular spot, it is worth the wait.
Be prepared to wait if you come on a weekend. Wish there were more tables.

I m soooo picky about fish. But this place is wonderful!!! All I can say is free a time to stop by and grab some fish and chips. No dine-in due to COVID. So, be prepared for a place to enjoy your lunch.

From out of province and I absolutely loved this place the first time I tried it. When I returned I planned to go here, and when I returned this place was on the top of my life (literally dreaming of the fish and chips for the past 3 years) but when I arrived on a Monday afternoon, it was closed, despite Google telling me that it opened today at 11:30. So sad because I leave tomorrow and won t be able to get it now. A whole trip planned around a fish and chips establishment that I didn t even get to enjoy, but 5 stars because it would have been worth it (based on my experience 3 years ago)

best fish and chips that I ever had this is not just a hype. fish was soft and tasty covered in crunchy batter. Line up starts before they open make sure to be there early. definitely a must go when you visit Granville Island.
All the staff were super kind and the fish and chips we had was PERFECT!
Halibut was nice and thick.  Wish they included more tartar sauce. If the gates (near the dock) are closed, you will have to go around to get to the restaurant.
Best place for fish and chips as well as other options too. The foods are very fresh and tasty

The halibut was really fresh. The tartar sauce is not a conventional dill flavour, but is very thick and creamy. I think it s tarragon instead- really good. The coleslaw is also unconventional, it s Asian inspired. Personally I like it a bit more zingy but it was a really solid fish and chip platter.
Solid food and chill workers! The fish tacos were spectacular! Definitely a must try.
The fish and chips was good but even if it wasn t good I still would ve giving 5 stars because of the girl that took my order. She was very sweet

Fish was nice and crispy on the outside, flakey on the inside. Very fresh! Fries were seasoned well and you can really distinctly taste the dill in the tartar sauce. Just sucks that we couldnt eat it within the premises but its COVID season so understandable.
What a gem! Had the albacore tuna sandwich and it was a 10/10! The staff are super friendly and obviously do a fantastic job. Will be back for sure!
Top notch fish and chips, very friendly staff. 100% recommend.
We had the greatest food at this cute little shop while visiting Canada. Highly recommended. We had halibut fish and chips, and the salmon sandwich. Amazing!!

Probably the best fish and chips I have had so far. One of the local favorites around the area. They have an amazing fried Oyster sandwich but sold out when we went. We usually order the halibut fish with extra tartar sauce. The line up and wait time is usually 30 to 45 mins but if you go between lunch and dinner hour might be less. This is a must try if you visit grandville Island. Will definitely go back, they never disappoint.
Great fish and chips, happy service and a waterfront location and view of Granville Island. Simple, outdoor bench seating or takeaway.

Fresh and tasty! Amazing people! Small business making great impact. Go Fish was recommended by my colleague, and yes, Go Fish ticked all the boxes! Clean and lovely environment. I love it! I will sure go back anytime I visit Vancouver again.
Went here on a recommendation from our walking tour guide. Great location and excellent food, Id go every week if I lived in Vancouver
The best fish n chips place in Vancouver! The fish was fresh and fries were fried to perfection! Its worth paying more for the halibut fillet.

(IG: KEVIFONG) The best Fish n Chips stall in Vancouver. Its located along the ocean side of Granville Island. Their ingredients are always fresh. I usually order the Halibut Fish n Chips, it is fried in a light batter that is served with fries/coleslaw then beautifully plated onto a Bamboo Steamer. I also recommend the Oyster Po-boy Sandwich.

Fantastic fish and chips. This place is a hidden gem near Granville island. Really small and often busy  shack .  Usually a line up but worth the wait. Located on the waters edge it serves some incredibly delicious seafood and chips. Worth a trip to get some. I highly recommend stopping by.
